The Eastern Cape family of a medical student, who died in Cuba, has left to fetch his body. Sibusiso Qongqo passed away in April and repatriating his remains has been an agonising battle for his family. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Eastern Cape family of a medical student, who died in Cuba, has left to fetch his body. Sibusiso Qongqo passed away in April and repatriating his remains has been an agonising battle for his family. Authorities came to their rescue after several failed attempts amid the COVID-19 pandemic. WATCH: Family wants student doctor's remains returned from Cuba After a protracted struggle, the family’s wish has been granted and they are heading to Havana to fetch his remains. Qongqo’s mother hopes this journey will end the dark chapter for their family.